0quality%20of%20the%20information%20is%20solid%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20the%20podcasts%20I%20generated%20gave%20an%20accurate%20overview%20of%20the%20information%20I%20fed%20it%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20catch%20any%20inaccuracies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20any%20AI%20tool%20though%2C%20Audio%20Overviews%20isn't%20perfect.%20Google%20notes%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20screen%20that%20%26quot%3BNotebookLM%20may%20still%20sometimes%20give%20inaccurate%20responses%2C%20so%20you%20may%20want%20to%20confirm%20any%20facts%20independently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20I%20probably%20wouldn't%20use%20it%20alone%20to%20educate%20me%20on%20a%20topic%20I'm%20not%20at%20all%20familiar%20with%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20do%20your%20own%20research%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20anything%20is%20said%20that%20seems%20off%20or%20inaccurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20avid%20podcast%20listener%20though%2C%20I%20was%20pleasantly%20surprised%20by%20the%20tool.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-dump-announcements-feels-never-ending-gartner-analyst-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWith%20so%20many%20AI%20developments%20coming%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20rare%20that%20I'm%20left%20awestruck%20by%20a%20tool%20that's%20actually%20available%20to%20play%20around%20with%2C%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAudio%20Overviews%20is%20probably%20my%20favorite%20AI%20tool%20I've%20tried%20out%20so%20far%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20showcases%20the%20innovative%20ways%20AI%20can%20be%20used%20in%20our%20daily%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-notebooklm-audio-overviews-ai-podcast-tool-2024-01%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728293402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fc57255ccfc192a5524f23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-notebooklm-audio-overviews-ai-podcast-tool-2024-01%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google's%20NotebookLM%20recently%20launched%20Audio%20Overviews.%20The%20AI%20podcasts%20sound%20surprisingly%20realistic%20and%20I%20found%20the%20info%20generally%20accurate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boomers%20spent%20their%20lives%20accumulating%20stuff.%20Now%20their%20kids%20are%20stuck%20with%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mountain%20of%20antique%20items%20with%20a%20cutout%20in%20the%20shape%20of%20a%20person%20with%20their%20arms%20on%20their%20hips%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20pile%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67001481198738e3a70e5361%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20iStock%3B%20Natalie%20Ammari%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20time%20Dale%20Sperling's%20mother%20pops%20by%20for%20her%20weekly%20visit%2C%20she%20brings%20with%20her%20a%20possession%20she%20wants%20to%20pass%20on.%20To%20Sperling%2C%20the%20drop-offs%20make%20it%20feel%20as%20if%20her%20mom%20is%20%26quot%3Bdumping%20her%20house%20into%20my%20house.%26quot%3B%20The%20most%20recent%20offload%20attempt%20was%20a%20collection%20of%20silver%20platters%2C%20which%20Sperling%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWho%20has%20time%20to%20use%20silver%3F%20You%20have%20to%20actually%20polish%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%2C%20'Mom%2C%20I%20would%20really%20love%20to%20take%20it%2C%20but%20what%20am%20I%20going%20to%20do%20with%20it%3F'%20So%20she's%20dejected.%20She%20puts%20it%20back%20in%20her%20car.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20that%20Sperling%2C%2046%2C%20wants%20to%20be%20rude%20to%20her%20baby-boomer%20mother%3B%20it's%20just%20that%20she%20has%20plenty%20of%20her%20own%20stuff.%20Plus%2C%20her%20father%20died%20in%202021%2C%20and%20they're%20still%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20with%20everything%20he%20had.%20He%20owned%20an%20arcade%20in%20New%20York%20City%20and%20amassed%20closets%20full%20of%20collectibles%20%E2%80%94%20magazines%2C%20posters%2C%20memorabilia%2C%20coins%2C%20buttons.%20Her%20mother%20is%20too%20upset%20to%20look%20at%20it%2C%20so%20little%20by%20little%2C%20Sperling%20and%20her%20sister%20have%20been%20going%20through%20everything.%20Deciding%20what%20to%20do%20with%20a%20lifetime%20of%20things%20is%20a%20monumental%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can't%20just%20rot%20in%20her%20basement%2C%20and%20then%20what%3F%26quot%3B%20Sperling%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESperling's%20parents%20thought%20everything%20they%20were%20accumulating%20was%20going%20to%20be%20worth%20money%2C%20so%20they%20saved%20it.%20And%20sure%2C%20maybe%20some%20of%20the%20posters%20would%20sell%20for%20%2440%20on%20Facebook%20Marketplace%2C%20but%20who%20really%20wants%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20hassle%3F%20Sperling's%20mom%20brought%20over%20her%20dad's%20penny%20collection%20for%20her%20kids%20to%20go%20through.%20It%20seemed%20like%20a%20fun%20activity%20at%20first%2C%20but%20it%20got%20old%20fast%2C%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest%26quot%3B%20penny%20they%20found%20was%20worth%20about%20%246.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20the%20volume%20of%20things%20that%20we'll%20have%20to%20go%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20stuff.%20It's%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESperling's%20conundrum%20is%20familiar%20to%20many%20people%20with%20parents%20facing%20down%20their%20golden%20years%3A%20After%20they've%20acquired%20things%20for%20decades%2C%20eventually%2C%20those%20things%20have%20to%20go.%20As%20the%20saying%20goes%2C%20you%20can't%20take%20it%20with%20you.%20Many%20millennials%2C%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20now%20facing%20the%20question%20of%20what%20to%20do%20with%20their%20parents'%20and%20grandparents'%20possessions%20as%20their%20loved%20ones%20downsize%20or%20die.%20Some%20boomers%20are%20even%20still%20managing%20the%20process%20with%20their%20parents.%20The%20process%20can%20be%20arduous%2C%20overwhelming%2C%20and%20painful.%20It's%20tough%20to%20look%20your%20mom%20in%20the%20eye%20and%20tell%20her%20that%20you%20don't%20want%20her%20prized%20wedding%20china%20or%20that%20giant%20brown%20hutch%20she%20keeps%20it%20in.%20For%20that%20matter%2C%20nobody%20else%20wants%20it%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%20that%20we%20live%20in%20a%20world%20that%20is%20overinundated%20with%20stuff%2C%20and%20the%20value%20of%20things%20that%20people%20hold%20dear%20and%20that%20they%20paid%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20for%20and%20they%20think%20retained%20value%20is%20not%20so%20much%2C%20which%20is%20unfortunate%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarah%20Hersh%2C%20a%20co-owner%20of%20Ben%20Hersh%20Estate%20Sales%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20more%20stuff%20than%20we%20need%2C%20and%20less%20of%20it%20is%20desirable%20to%20other%20people%20than%20we%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20has%20been%20made%20of%20the%20impending%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-millionaires-baby-boomer-inheritance-wealth-transfer-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egreat%20wealth%20transfer%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20as%20baby%20boomers%20and%20the%20Silent%20Generation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cerulli.com%2Fpress-releases%2Fcerulli-anticipates-84-trillion-in-wealth-transfers-through-2045%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epass%20on%20a%20combined%20%2484.4%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20wealth%20to%20younger%20generations.%20Getting%20less%20attention%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bgreat%20stuff%20transfer%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20everybody%20has%20to%20decipher%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20older%20generations'%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20finding%20unilaterally%20across%20the%20board%2C%20pretty%20much%20without%20exception%20%E2%80%94%20you'll%20get%20a%20random%20exception%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20millennials%20are%20saying%2C%20'No%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20your%20stuff.%20I%20barely%20want%20my%20stuff%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Mary%20Kay%20Buysse%2C%20co-executive%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Senior%20%26amp%3B%20Specialty%20Move%20Managers%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20trade%20association.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20this%20is%20a%20timeless%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20every%20generation%20accumulates%20things%2C%20and%20younger%20generations%20rebel%20against%20older%20generations'%20tastes.%20But%20the%20sheer%20size%20of%20the%20current%20problem%20is%20unprecedented%20given%20that%20baby%20boomers%20are%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-baby-boomers-became-the-most-selfish-generation-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextra-materialistic%20breed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20time%20of%20economic%20prosperity%2C%20were%20raised%20by%20parents%20for%20whom%20the%20Great%20Depression%20loomed%20large%2C%20and%20hit%20their%20prime%20in%20the%20'80s%2C%20when%20people%20were%20driving%20around%20with%20bumper%20stickers%20reading%2C%20%26quot%3BHe%20who%20dies%20with%20the%20most%20toys%20wins.%26quot%3B%20They're%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollectibles-collectors-items-worthless-not-valuable-today%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollectors%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20they%20stocked%20up%20on%20Hummel%20figurines%20and%20Bing%20%26amp%3B%20Gr%C3%B8ndahl%20plates%20and%20picked%20up%20a%20souvenir%20every%20time%20they%20went%20on%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20boomers%20love%20stuff%2C%20and%20not%20just%20their%20stuff.%20They%20held%20on%20to%20their%20parents'%20stuff%20when%20they%20inherited%20it%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20are%20sitting%20with%20their%20kids'%20stuff%20in%20their%20attics%20now%2C%20too.%20Sometimes%2C%20the%20sheer%20task%20of%20organizing%20and%20purging%20is%20so%20daunting%20that%20retirees%20who%20are%20ready%20and%20excited%20to%20move%20don't%2C%20opting%20instead%20to%20stay%20put%20with%20their%20collection%20of%20trinkets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20three%20generations%20of%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20Mindy%20Godding%2C%20a%20professional%20organizer%20and%20the%20owner%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abundanceorganizing.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAbundance%20Organizing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%20And%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-wont-sell-homes-millennials-kids-need-housing-affordability-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboomers%20have%20famously%20been%20remaining%20in%20their%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20even%20worse.%20%26quot%3BThe%20longer%20it's%20been%20since%20you've%20been%20through%20a%20major%20transition%2C%20like%20a%20move%20or%20renovation%2C%20the%20more%20things%20can%20pile%20up%20and%20accumulate%20in%20the%20nooks%20and%20crannies%20in%20your%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Godding%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20ideal%20scenario%2C%20families%20would%20gather%20with%20plenty%20of%20time%20on%20hand%20to%20cull%20everything.%20Parents%20figure%20out%20who%20among%20their%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20want%20what%2C%20what%20lands%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bkeep%26quot%3B%20pile%2C%20what's%20worth%20money%2C%20and%20what%20can%20hopefully%20be%20donated.%20(Though%20FYI%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20Goodwill%20stores%20no%20longer%20take%20furniture.)%20But%20life%20is%20often%20not%20an%20ideal%20scenario%20%E2%80%94%20families%20instead%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20fire-sale%20situation%2C%20where%20a%20parent%20is%20ill%20and%20needs%20to%20move%20fast%2C%20or%20a%20loved%20one%20has%20died%2C%20or%20just%20nobody%20realized%20how%20long%20any%20of%20this%20would%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20people%20don't%20realize%20when%20they're%20acquiring%20across%2050%2C%2060%2C%2070%2C%2080%20years%20is%20that%20it%20actually%20costs%20a%20lot%20or%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20it%20as%20well%2C%20and%20often%20that%20is%20in%20a%20time%20when%20people%20are%20in%20a%20crisis%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20Elizabeth%20Hirsh%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20Downsizers%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20logistical%20issues%2C%20family%20dynamics%20are%20complicated.%20Styles%20change%2C%20and%20younger%20generations%20often%20don't%20like%20or%20need%20the%20things%20their%20parents%20have%2C%20but%20explaining%20that%20can%20be%20tricky.%20Sure%2C%20everybody%20wants%20Mom's%20ring%2C%20but%20nobody%20knows%20what%20to%20do%20with%20that%20spoon%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20tough%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wen%20Stone%2C%20a%20high-end%20estate%20liquidator%20in%20Dallas%20with%20his%20mother%2C%20Janelle.%20%26quot%3BThe%20parents%20are%20just%20scared%20and%20guilty%2C%20and%20the%20kids%20are%20guilty%20to%20say%20no.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrying%20to%20smooth%20over%20generational%20differences%20in%20taste%20can%20be%20knotty.%20Millennials%20are%20more%20mobile%20than%20their%20parents.%20They're%20also%20more%20minimalist%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20and%20they%20love%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gray-home-interiors-generational-stereotype-tiktok2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennial%20gray%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Boomers%20got%20a%20kick%20out%20of%20having%20a%20bunch%20of%20trinkets%20from%20their%20travels%20and%20big%20brown%20furniture%20and%20colorful%20glassware%20and%20fancy%20china.%20Their%20kids%20don't%20even%20have%20a%20dining%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20children%20are%20looking%20around%20at%20this%20volume%20of%20possessions%20and%20are%20completely%20overwhelmed%2C%26quot%3B%20Godding%20said.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20parents%20are%20also%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20stuff%2C%20and%20it's%20almost%20like%20an%20avoidance%20strategy%20of%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I'll%20just%20have%20my%20kids%20deal%20with%20it.'%20Nobody%20wants%20to%20take%20this%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20what-to-do-with-all-this-stuff%20conundrum%20has%20two%20sides%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20financial%20and%20sentimental.%20As%20more%20people%20confront%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20a%20whole%20cottage%20industry%20of%20downsizers%2C%20estate%20sellers%2C%20and%20auctioneers%20has%20popped%20up%20to%20make%20the%20process%20easier%2C%20for%20a%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Ben%20Miller%2C%20a%20New%20York%20antique-silver%20specialist%20and%20the%20host%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BCurious%20Objects%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20part%20of%20his%20job%20is%20breaking%20people's%20hearts.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20amass%20so%20many%20things%20believing%20they'll%20be%20worth%20something%20someday%2C%20and%20are%20disappointed%20to%20find%20out%20when%20they%20aren't.%20Clients%20come%20to%20him%20with%2C%20say%2C%20a%20tea%20set%20their%20parents%20coveted%20for%20decades%2C%20firmly%20believing%20that%20when%20they%20died%2C%20their%20kids%20at%20the%20very%20least%20would%20be%20able%20to%20sell%20it%20for%20a%20nice%20return.%20Or%20they've%20been%20watching%20a%20lot%20of%20%26quot%3BAntiques%20Roadshow%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantiques-roadshow-veteran-learns-rolex-is-worth-700000-video-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey're%20hoping%20their%20trash%20is%20treasure%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20happy%20version%20of%20that%20story%20is%20they're%20right%2C%20and%20it%20is%20something%20that%20is%20really%20valuable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20much%20more%20common%20story%20is%20it's%20worth%20much%20less%20than%20they%20anticipated%2C%20or%20perhaps%20almost%20nothing%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20painful%20to%20watch.%20Miller%20tries%20to%20approach%20the%20situation%20with%20empathy.%20%26quot%3BI%20often%20emphasize%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20market%20value%20of%20the%20object%20and%20the%20sentimental%20value%20don't%20always%20go%20hand%20in%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20can%20be%20disappointing%20from%20a%20budgetary%20perspective%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20reason%20that%20has%20to%20be%20disappointing%20from%20an%20emotional%20perspective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20cognitive%20biases%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20the%20endowment%20effect%20%E2%80%94%20make%20us%20believe%20items%20we%20own%20are%20more%20valuable%20than%20they%20are%2C%20Stephanie%20Preston%2C%20a%20psychologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20said.%20And%20sometimes%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20abandon%20that%20notion.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20get%20yoked%20into%20how%20much%20they%20paid%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuysse%20recently%20took%20her%20wedding%20china%20to%20a%20church%20rummage%20sale.%20When%20she%20got%20it%20in%201978%2C%20it%20was%20worth%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%20The%20rummage-sale%20people%20put%20an%20%2480%20price%20tag%20on%20it%2C%20and%20it%20didn't%20sell.%20It's%20classic%20economics%3A%20supply%20and%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20the%20question%20of%20monetary%20value%20is%20settled%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20sentimental%20value%20remains%20and%20can%20be%20even%20more%20pertinent.%20A%20lot%20of%20parents%20hope%20their%20kids%20will%20want%20their%20things%2C%20but%20they%20don't.%20Those%20can%20be%20tough%20conversations%20on%20both%20sides.%20It's%20difficult%20to%20throw%20away%20things%20that%20mean%20something%20to%20you.%20It's%20also%20a%20challenge%20to%20tell%20a%20loved%20one%20that%20you%20don't%20want%20the%20thing%20they%20loved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20really%20common%20for%20us%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20items%20because%20we%20feel%20an%20obligation%20to%20take%20care%20of%20that%20item%20on%20behalf%20of%20someone%20that%20we've%20loved%20and%20usually%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20Godding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20leads%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20deferred%20decisions%20%E2%80%94%20too%20many%20items%20wind%20up%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bmaybe%26quot%3B%20pile%2C%20or%20they%20end%20up%20taking%20begrudging%20space%20in%20the%20garage.%20Or%2C%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20they%20land%20in%20a%20storage%20unit%2C%20which%20every%20professional%20I%20spoke%20with%20for%20this%20story%20said%20is%20a%20big%20no-no.%20Dad%20puts%20stuff%20in%20storage%2C%20pays%20%24150%20a%20month%20on%20it%20for%2010%20years%2C%20dies%2C%20and%20suddenly%20everyone%20realizes%20he%20spent%20%2418%2C000%20housing%20items%20nobody%20still%20wants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNever%20get%20a%20storage%20unit%2C%26quot%3B%20Janelle%20Stone%20from%20Dallas%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20cuss%20word.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPractically%20everyone%20I've%20told%20about%20this%20story%20in%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20weeks%20has%20had%20a%20personal%20anecdote%20to%20share%20about%20the%20impending%20avalanche%20of%20boomer%20stuff.%20One%20person%20had%20promised%20to%20take%20her%20in-laws'%20dining%20set%2C%20even%20though%20she%20has%20no%20space%20for%20it%20because%20she%20already%20has%20the%20one%20from%20her%20parents.%20Those%20same%20in-laws%20have%20what%20she%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bpathological%20obsession%20with%20not%20giving%20away%20their%20china.%26quot%3B%20Another%20is%20navigating%20his%20father's%20early%20dementia%20diagnosis%2C%20which%20entails%20both%20figuring%20out%20Medicare%20and%20digging%20through%20his%20parents'%20basement%2C%20which%20is%20filled%20with%20his%20grandparents'%20stuff.%20When%20his%20daughter%20was%20born%2C%20his%20parents%20gave%20him%20a%20play%20kitchen%20he%20and%20his%20sister%20had%20used%20in%20the%20'80s.%20%26quot%3BNow%20I%20have%20it%20in%20my%20basement%20for%20the%20next%2030%20years%3F%20Until%20my%20kid%20has%20a%20kid%3F%20And%20I%20bequeath%20her%20a%20wooden%20box%20with%20a%20stove%20painted%20on%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20my%20own%20version%20of%20this%2C%20with%20my%20mom%2C%20who%20inherited%20and%20held%20on%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20stuff%20from%20my%20dad's%20side%20of%20the%20family%2C%20I%20imagine%20at%20least%20in%20part%20out%20of%20a%20sense%20of%20obligation.%20She%20keeps%20it%20in%20a%20room%20in%20her%20house%20I've%20come%20to%20think%20of%20as%20the%20lair%20of%20the%20creepy%20%E2%80%94%20she's%20got%20scary-looking%20old%20dolls%2C%20an%20oil%20painting%20of%20some%20ancestor%20where%20the%20eyes%20follow%20you%20around%20the%20room%2C%20an%20old%2C%20heavy%20hutch%20with%20God%20knows%20what%20in%20it.%20The%20whole%20room%20screams%20%26quot%3Bhaunted%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20want%20basically%20nothing%20in%20it%2C%20but%20when%20she%20decides%20to%20downsize%2C%20that's%20all%20supposed%20to%20be%20for%20me.%20Last%20year%2C%20she%20tried%20to%20persuade%20me%20to%20take%20my%20aunt's%20old%20fur%20coat.%20I%20resisted%2C%20so%20it%20remains%20in%20her%20closet.%20Nobody%20wants%20it.%20Everybody%20feels%20too%20guilty%20to%20give%20it%20away.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20my%20Barbies%20and%20high-school%20trophies%20and%20even%20the%20prom%20dress%20she's%20still%20holding%20on%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20the%20experts%20in%20downsizing%20and%20estates%20for%20advice%20for%20families%20facing%20the%20great%20stuff%20transfer.%20They%20said%20to%20start%20early%20%E2%80%94%20hopefully%20before%20you're%20urgently%20moving%20someone%20to%20assisted%20living%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20know%20this%20will%20take%20longer%20than%20you%20think.%20There's%20no%20flying%20in%20on%20a%20Friday%20afternoon%20and%20renting%20a%20dumpster%2C%20then%20getting%20out%20of%20town%20on%20Sunday.%20Conversations%20about%20what%20to%20do%20with%20someone's%20prized%20possessions%20can%20be%20emotional%2C%20and%20people%20often%20need%20time%20and%20space%20to%20process.%20As%20you%20go%20through%20your%20loved%20one's%20things%2C%20ask%20them%20for%20the%20stories%20behind%20them%20if%20you%20can.%20Remember%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20stuff%20to%20live%20a%20full%20life%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20let%20go%20of%20it.%20It%20may%20also%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20a%20really%20nice%20bonding%20experience.%20Even%20if%20a%20family%20member%20doesn't%20want%20a%20certain%20object%2C%20sometimes%20knowing%20it's%20going%20somewhere%20good%20is%20satisfying%20%E2%80%94%20to%20a%20secondhand%20store%20or%20a%20homeless%20shelter%20or%20a%20refugee%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20practical%20level%2C%20downsizers%20said%20to%20start%20with%20the%20small%2C%20easy%20spaces.%20It%20helps%20develop%20the%20decision%20muscle%20for%20when%20the%20big%2C%20hard%20parts%20come.%20Don't%20trust%20listing%20prices%20on%20eBay%20%E2%80%94%20look%20at%20how%20much%20things%20are%20actually%20selling%20for.%20Get%20a%20professional%20to%20help%20if%20you%20need%20it.%20No%20%26quot%3Bmaybe%26quot%3B%20piles.%20And%20if%20someone%20really%20insists%20you%20take%20something%2C%20you%20might%20just%20want%20to%20say%20yes%2C%20because%20what%20they're%20trying%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20is%20the%20burden%20of%20the%20item%20more%20than%20the%20item%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20saying%20that%20you%20can't%20get%20rid%20of%20it%20once%20you%20take%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cameron%20Huddleston%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BMom%20and%20Dad%2C%20We%20Need%20to%20Talk%3A%20How%20to%20Have%20Essential%20Conversations%20With%20Your%20Parents%20About%20Their%20Finances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertain%20items%20might%20come%20back%20into%20fashion%20%E2%80%94%20St