%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20becoming%20a%20VC%2C%20Tully%20worked%20at%20startups%20and%20led%20engineering%20teams%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Tully%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20computers%20and%20games%20have%20always%20been%20a%20core%20part%20of%20his%20life.%20He%20had%20an%20Apple%20II%20computer%20and%20cassette%20tape%20player%20that%20plugged%20into%20a%20TV%20on%20a%20rolling%20cart%2C%20which%20is%20where%20he%20taught%20himself%20to%20code%20by%20playing%20video%20games%20and%20reading%20through%20manuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20an%20early%20game%20of%20his%2C%20coded%20using%20Applesoft%20BASIC%2C%20was%20a%20text-based%20adventure%20game%20in%20which%20players%20would%20get%20lost%20in%20a%20forest%20and%20navigate%20through%20a%20maze%2C%20answering%20a%20series%20of%20fork-in-the-road%20puzzles%20to%20chase%20down%20the%20treasure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20teenager%2C%20Tully%20had%20a%20bank%20of%20modems%20at%20his%20mom's%20house%20to%20organize%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ftechnology%2Farchive%2F2016%2F11%2Fthe-lost-civilization-of-dial-up-bulletin-board-systems%2F506465%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebulletin%20board%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20a%20pre-internet%20computer%20server%20that%20other%20users%20could%20dial%20into%20%E2%80%93%20to%20host%20pirated%20video%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20college%2C%20Tully%20gravitated%20towards%20startups%2C%20becoming%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Dot-com%20era%20companies%20iScale%20and%20Pillar%20Data%20Systems%2C%20the%20latter%20of%20which%20was%20acquired%20by%20Oracle%20in%202003.%20He%20then%20spent%20the%20next%2014%20years%20at%20Yahoo%2C%20working%20his%20way%20up%20to%20lead%20engineering%20for%20Yahoo!%2C%20AOL%2C%20and%20its%20media%20properties%2C%20which%20included%20Huffington%20Post%2C%20Tumblr%2C%20Polyvore%2C%20and%20Flurry%2C%20and%20managing%20a%20team%20of%20more%20than%20850%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Tully%20joined%20data%20analytics%20company%20Splunk%20as%20its%20chief%20technology%20officer%20and%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20product%20and%20engineering%20and%20managed%20the%20company's%20migration%20to%20the%20cloud.%20While%20he%20loved%20his%20team%20at%20Splunk%2C%20Tully%20said%20that%20he%20was%20always%20interested%20in%20the%20investing%20side%20of%20the%20tech%20world%2C%20and%20his%20interest%20was%20further%20piqued%20by%20his%20wife%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsequoia-partner-jess-lee-advice-for-startup-founders-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJess%20Lee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20has%20been%20a%20partner%20at%20Sequoia%20since%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrowing%20up%20in%20the%20Valley%2C%20I%20had%20this%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20that%20as%20a%20technical%20person%2C%20I%20could%20do%20the%20job%20differently%2C%20so%20I%20began%20to%20take%20some%20calls%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20those%20calls%20eventually%20turned%20into%20a%20job%20offer%20at%20Menlo%20Ventures%2C%20and%20Tully%20joined%20the%20firm%20as%20a%20partner%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20an%20opportunity%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20next%20wave%20of%20folks%20that%20joined%20the%20firm%2C%20which%20was%20exciting%20to%20me%20because%20I'm%20a%20builder%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a315a417-ba6a-45c5-83f4-c8198dfb0b19%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20Menlo%20Ventures%2C%20Tully%20writes%20checks%20for%20AI%20startups%20at%20the%20app%20and%20infrastructure%20layers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20joining%20Menlo%2C%20Tully%20has%20invested%20in%20nine%20startups%2C%20including%20Pinecone%2C%20which%20raised%20a%20%2428%20million%20Series%20A%20in%202022%3B%20Neon%2C%20which%20raised%20a%20%2446%20million%20Series%20B%20in%202023%3B%20Unstructured%2C%20which%20raised%20a%20%2440%20million%20Series%20B%20in%202024%3B%20and%20JuliaHub%2C%20an%20AI%20programming%20startup%20that%20raised%20%2424%20million%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20of%20his%20portfolio%20companies%2C%20AI%20quality%20management%20software%20startup%20True%20Era%2C%20was%20acquired%20by%20Snowflake%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Tully%2C%20finding%20camaraderie%20with%20technical%20founders%20has%20been%20a%20winning%20strategy%20so%20far%20in%20his%20VC%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20background%20helps%20me%20connect%20with%20technical%20founders%20because%20they%20want%20investors%20who%20they%20can%20talk%20shop%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20managed%20teams%20and%20have%20been%20CTO%20of%20a%20public%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20also%20written%20code%20as%20a%20way%20to%20help%20win%20over%20startups%20in%20the%20broader%20Menlo%20Ventures%20portfolio.%20In%202022%2C%20another%20Menlo%20partner%2C%20Naomi%20Pilosof%20Ionita%2C%20was%20working%20to%20land%20a%20deal%20for%20fintech%20startup%20Orb.%20The%20company%20didn't%20have%20a%20software%20development%20kit%2C%20so%20Tully%20wrote%20them%20one%2C%20printed%20out%20a%20link%20to%20the%20devkit%2C%20rolled%20it%20into%20a%20scroll%2C%20and%20delivered%20it%20to%20the%20startup.%20That%20helped%20seal%20the%20deal%2C%20and%20Ionita%20led%20Orb's%20%2414%20million%20Series%20A%20funding%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Menlo%20has%20been%20bolstering%20its%20portfolio%20with%20AI%20infrastructure%20startups%2C%20Tully%20said%20he's%20excited%20these%20days%20about%20opportunities%20at%20the%20application%20layer.%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20this%20means%20looking%20at%20various%20vertical%20AI%20categories%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F15-legal-tech-startups-ai-raised-most-vc-funding-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegaltech%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20he%20wrote%20a%20%2414%20million%20seed%20check%20for