ee-speech-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplications%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Brazil%20for%20the%20company%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20August%2C%20Brazil's%20Supreme%20Court%20banned%20the%20platform%20for%20failing%20to%20comply%20with%20orders%20related%20to%20content%20moderation%20and%20for%20not%20appointing%20a%20legal%20representative%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20social%20media%20platform%20was%20also%20slapped%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-x-hit-with-last-fine-before-reinstatement-brazil-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%245.2%20million%20fine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20X's%20legal%20team%20submitted%20documents%20showing%20that%20they%20paid%20the%20fines.%20But%20the%20court%20said%20that%20the%20money%20had%20been%20sent%20to%20the%20wrong%20bank%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20the%20money%20must%20be%20redirected%20to%20the%20correct%20account%20before%20it%20can%20consider%20lifting%20X's%20ban%20in%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20lawyers%20maintain%20that%20the%20company%20has%20correctly%20paid%20the%20fines%2C%20Reuters%20reported%2C%20which%20is%20the%20last%20hurdle%20the%20company%20has%20to%20overcome%20before%20being%20allowed%20to%20resume%20operations%20in%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrazil%20was%20one%20of%20X's%20key%20markets%2C%20with%20around%2021.5%20million%20users%2C%20making%20it%20the%20sixth-largest%20user%20base%20for%20the%20platform%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fx-asks-brazils-top-court-allow-it-resume-services-source-says-2024-09-26%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBrazil%2520was%2520X%2527s%2520sixth%252Dbiggest%2Cwith%2520about%252021.5%2520million%2520users.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20platform's%20legal%20troubles%20in%20the%20country%20have%20stirred%20