g%20business%2C%20and%20I%20have%20faced%20bureaucracy%20when%20setting%20up%20my%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20had%20to%20make%20sacrifices%20as%20a%20family%20too.%20My%20wife%20is%20still%20working%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%20and%20spends%20much%20more%20time%20commuting%20than%20she%20did%20back%20in%20the%20US.%20I%20have%20two%20daughters%2C%20and%20inequality%20in%20Indian%20workplaces%20and%20concerns%20for%20their%20safety%20also%20weigh%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20a%20different%20joy%20in%20building%20solutions%20for%20India%20and%20the%20problems%20that%20I%20grew%20up%20around%2C%20like%20improving%20local%20greenery%20and%20better%20access%20to%20mentorship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20big%20advantage%20is%20that%20the%20Indian%20market%20is%20chaotic.%20Even%20long-established%20players%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20figure%20it%20out%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20new%20entrants.%20The%20market%20size%20has%20also%20been%20encouraging.%20One%20of%20our%20first%20orders%20came%20from%20the%20opposite%20end%20of%20the%20country%2C%20which%20was%20surprising%20because%20we%20had%20not%20even%20begun%20marketing%20or%20search%20engine%20optimization%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20most%20importantly%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20found%20what%20was%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20I%20heard%20my%20parents%20talking%20about%20their%20regrets%20and%20things%20they%20wanted%20to%20do.%20I%20didn't%20want%20any%20regrets%20when%20telling%20my%20kids%20about%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20myself%3A%20I'll%20explore%20my%20own%20venture%20for%20five%20to%2010%20years%20and%20go%20back%20to%20a%20corporate%20job%20if%20things%20don't%20work%20out.%20I'll%20have%20a%20bigger%20experience%20and%20a%20better%20story%20to%20tell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDid%20you%20leave%20Big%20Tech%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20in%20a%20completely%20different%20field%3F%20Please%20reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%3A%