%20The%20guardian%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20wolves%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahuadanr%20Wolf%20Sanctuary%20in%20Jharkhand%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20sanctuary%20in%20India%20dedicated%20to%20wolf%20preservation%20%E2%80%94%20owes%20its%20existence%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F300043%2Fforgotten-forest-officer-sp-shahi-behind-indias-only-wolf-sanctuary-mahuadanr-jharkhand%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%20P%20Shahi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20and%20forest%20officer.%20Back%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20he%20paid%20close%20attention%20to%20how%20wolves%20were%20hurtling%20towards%20extinction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20noted%20how%20unlike%20most%20forest%20officers%20of%20his%20era%2C%20Shahi%20recognised%20the%20importance%20of%20what%20we%20now%20call%20%E2%80%98Open%20Natural%20Ecosystems%E2%80%99%20for%20wolves.%20These%20ecosystems%20consist%20of%20a%20range%20of%20non-forested%20habitats%20from%20savanna%20grasslands%20to%20deserts%2C%20which%20host%20a%20high%20density%20of%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20mammalian%20fauna%E2%80%9D.%20What%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20interesting%20about%20these%20ecosystems%20is%20that%20unlike%20wildlife%20sanctuaries%20and%20other%20protected%20areas%20where%20limits%20are%20set%20on%20human%20habitation%2C%20they%20support%20the%20lives%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20pastoralists%20and%20their%20livestock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SP%20Shahi%20%26amp%3B%20the%20Indian%20grey%20wolf%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2FSP-Shahi-Mahuadanr-Wolves-Feature-Image-2-1665669212-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-300065%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESP%20Shahi%20%26amp%3B%20the%20Indian%20grey%20wolf%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20like%20Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%2C%20Shahi%20also%20understood%20the%20role%20of%20local%20communities%20(in%20this%20case%20pastoralists)%20in%20facilitating%20conservation.%20Beyond%20wolves%2C%20Shahi%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20Palamau%20and%20his%20meticulous%20documentation%20of%20its%20wildlife%20was%20a%20very%20key%20reason%20that%20this%20forest%20was%20declared%20as%20tiger%20reserves%20in%201973%2C%20according%20to%20P%20K%20Sen%2C%20former%20director%20of%20Project%20Tiger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20J%20Vijaya%3A%20The%20defender%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20turtles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%2018%20April%201987%2C%20the%20bodily%20remains%20of%20J%20Vijaya%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20female%20herpetologist%20and%20turtle%20field%20biologist%2C%20were%20found%20in%20Guindy%20National%20Park%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Only%2028%2C%20the%20cause%20of%20her%20death%20remains%20unknown%20to%20this%20day%20but%20what%20remains%20undeniable%20is%20the%20legacy%20she%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20off%20as%20a%20volunteer%20at%20Madras%20Snake%20Park%20in%201975%20as%20a%20college%20student%2C%20Vijaya%20(known%20to%20her%20friends%20as%20%E2%80%98Viji%E2%80%99)%20would%20go%20on%20to%20not%20only%20become%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20researchers%20of%20turtles%20but%20also%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20its%20conservation.%20To%20understand%20the%20scope%20of%20turtle%20trade%20and%20the%20exploitation%20it%20entailed%2C%20she%20would%20travel%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20this%20country%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98badlands%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Chambal%20(ravines)%20to%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20tribute%20penned%20by%20freelance%20journalist%20Janaki%20Lenin%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fecologise.in%2F2017%2F04%2F18%2Ftribute-viji-turtle-girl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEcologise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20black%20and%20white%20pictures%20she%20took%20of%20the%20gory%20Ridley%20sea%20turtle%20slaughter%20on%20Digha%20beach%20and%20in%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Calcutta%2C%20shook%20the%20public%20when%20India%20Today%20magazine%20ran%20them%20in%20the%20early%201980s.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20media%20expose%20ever%20done%20on%20the%20free-for-all%20trade%20in%20sea%20turtles%20and%20highlights%20the%20difference%20one%20individual%20can%20make%20for%20conservation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20her%20expose%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20immediately%20took%20action%20against%20the%20exploitation%20of%20sea%20turtles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Anne%20Wright%3A%20India%E2%80%99s%20adopted%20daughter%20and%20pioneer%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%204%20October%2C%202023%2C%20India%20mourned%20the%20loss%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F333222%2Fanne-wright-conservationist-wildlife-protection-act-reserves-project-tiger-legacy-raza-kazmi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20who%20dedicated%20over%20five%20decades%20to%20protecting%20India%E2%80%99s%20wildlife.%20This%20daughter%20of%20a%20British%20civil%20servant%20decided%20to%20adopt%20India%20as%20%E2%80%98her%20country%E2%80%99%20and%20worked%20tirelessly%20to%20protect%20its%20fauna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnne%20was%20a%20true%20changemaker%2C%20breaking%20gender%20barriers%20in%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20playing%20a%20key%20role%20in%20drafting%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%20of%201972%2C%20and%20driving%20the%20creation%20of%20numerous%20Protected%20Areas%2C%20including%20Palamau%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20Dalma%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary.%20She%20worked%20closely%20with%20local%20communities%20and%20bureaucracies%20to%20make%20lasting%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Late%20Anne%20Wright%20receiving%20an%20award%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333245%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELate%20Anne%20Wright%20receiving%20an%20award%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20working%20towards%20these%20critical%20causes%2C%20in%201970%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20an%20article%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Statesman%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20describes%20in%20harrowing%20detail%20the%20illegal%20sale%20of%20tiger%20and%20leopard%20skins%20in%20Kolkata.%20The%20article%20was%20republished%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20(NYT)%2C%20causing%20a%20global%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20article%20was%20debated%20heavily%20in%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%2C%20and%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20exaggeration%20to%20say%20that%20this%20article%2C%20along%20with%20the%20damning%20photographs%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20tiger%20hunting%20especially%20for%20skin%20trade%2C%20convinced%20the%20then%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20ban%20tiger%20hunting%20the%20very%20same%20year%20(1970).%20That%20was%20the%20power%20of%20her%20pen.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Saroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%3A%20A%20parent%20to%20the%20tigress%20Khairi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%205%20October%2C%201974%2C%20a%20female%20tiger%20cub%20was%20brought%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F233080%2Ftigress-khairi-simlipal-odisha-ifs-officer-saroj-raj-choudhury-documentary-pugmark-method-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESaroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20Field%20Director%20of%20the%20Similipal%20Tiger%20Reserve%20in%20the%20Mayurbhanj%20district%20of%20Odisha.%20Found%20unattended%20by%20people%20of%20the%20Kharia%20tribal%20community%2C%20Saroj%20would%20name%20her%20%E2%80%98Khairi%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20next%20seven%20years%2C%20Khairi%20would%20become%20a%20%E2%80%98free-living%20family%20member%E2%80%99%20at%20Choudhury%E2%80%99s%20official%20bungalow%20in%20Jashipur.%20She%20was%20fed%20with%20mutton%20and%20milk%20powder%2C%20slept%20on%20their%20beds%20and%20often%20played%20with%20them.%20Saroj%20closely%20observed%20her%20to%20study%20the%20various%20behavioural%20aspects%20of%20tigers%2C%20especially%20the%20use%20of%20pheromones%2C%20their%20mating%20behaviour%20and%20territoriality%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20long%20before%20Saroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%20took%20over%20as%20the%20Simlipal%20Tiger%20Reserve%E2%80%99s%20first%20Field%20Director%20and%20met%20Khairi%2C%20he%20had%20already%20established%20himself%20as%20a%20pioneer%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20particularly%20of%20tigers%2C%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20developing%20the%20pugmark%20tracking%20technique%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20the%20bedrock%20of%20organising%20tiger%20censuses%20in%20India%20till%202004%20and%20the%20foundation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20much%20vaunted%20Project%20Tiger%20initiative%20%E2%80%94%20to%20mentoring%20generations%20of%20forest%20officers%20in%20the%20finer%20nuances%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20Choudhury%20remains%20a%20legendary%20conservationist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F17145020%2FSaroj-Raj-Choudury-12.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22684%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Saroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%20with%20Khairi%20%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-233089%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22528%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESaroj%20Raj%20Choudhury%20with%20Khairi%20(Image%20courtesy%20Twitter%2FRamesh%20Pandey%20IFS)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20Images%20courtesy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFateh_Singh_Rathore%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%